'''Cosmetic textiles''' are the functional [[textile]]s, including [[garment]]s, underwear which come in direct contact with the skin through the process of [[microencapsulation]]. They concern the treatment of the skin for a cosmetic approach (for example, the orange peel effect), but can also be a vehicle for other active functions, such as slimming and body shaping. Cosmetic textiles currently offered on the market claim to be moisturizing, perfumed, [[cellulite]] reducing and body slimming.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.knittingindustry.com/beyond-beauty-the-future-of-cosmtotextiles/|title=Beyond Beauty: The Future of Cosmétotextiles}}</ref>

