The '''Koman culture''' is a culture that originated in the 6th through the 8th century [[AD]] around the area of [[Koman, Albania|Koman]], [[Albania]], and is considered to explain the transitioning from the [[Illyrians|Illyrian]] population to the [[Albanians|Albanian]] one.<ref name="Tsetskhladze2005">{{cite book|author=Gocha R. Tsetskhladze|title=Ancient West & East|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=6Xh14u9WmnYC&pg=PA230|accessdate=26 September 2013|year=2005|publisher=BRILL|isbn=978-90-04-14176-6|page=230}}</ref>
The earliest discoveries around the Koman culture were made in 1898, around the graveyard of the [[Dalmaca castle]], near Koman.<ref>{{cite book|title=Problems of the Formation of the Albanian People, Their Language, and Culture: (selection).|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=vZq4AAAAIAAJ|accessdate=26 September 2013|year=1984|publisher="8 Nëntori" Publishing House|page=73}}</ref>
